cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.CL

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on social network applications and modelling of users and locations based on spatio-temporal data. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes an embedding model based on feed-forward neural networks. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper discusses location recommendation based on the proposed Spatio-Temporal Embedding Similarity algorithm. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve software development for implementing the proposed model and algorithm. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also less likely but possible as the paper may involve natural language processing for processing social media check-ins.
